<item>
            <title>[SOLR-2791] Replication: abortfetch is broken if replication was started by fetchindex</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-2791</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If I start replication by issuing a &quot;fetchindex&quot; command with a &quot;masterUrl&quot; parameter, it seems to me (by looking at the trunk code) that &quot;abortfetch&quot; command would not do anything. &lt;br/&gt;
It appears to be aborting only when replication is configured with hardcoded master/slave cores.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The fix appears to be to use tempSnapPuller.abortPull always because tempSnapPuller is always the snap puller doing the actual work. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
